\begin_layout Standard
We maintain that studying question-asking dialogs about emotion shows the
 capability of humans to use a large, rich, subjective vocabulary of emotion
 words and provides a theory of emotion description that captures the shared
 meaning of natural language.
 The framework we present differs from other theories of emotion in that
 it aims to study how people describe emotions, rather than how emotions
 
\emph on
should be
\emph default
 described.
 As such, it can be seen as a descriptive, rather than prescriptive, theory,
 and hence has commonalities with sociological studies of emotions 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Shaver2001,King1989,Mihalcea2006,Kazemzadeh2012"

\end_inset

