 natural language should be relative to a particular agent or set of agents
 at a given time who hold similar beliefs and communicate using the same
 language.
 Rather than trying to establish a particular definition for emotion words,
 we study how shared meaning can be established through verbal behavior
 even when people may have different ways of describing emotions.
 
