 One exception where the natural language modality could be less sensitive
 is in the case of children and non-native speakers.
 In this case, we can imagine less fluent subjects who have conceptual distincti
ons in their beliefs about emotions that they are not able to verbally express
 without the aid of elicitation.
 Detangling the variability in cognitive and verbal capabilities is a challenge
 for the EMO20Q methodology though we could hypothesize that a verbal limitation
 would be observable in subjects requiring more questions, while cognitive
 limitations would be observable in subjects failing to guess correctly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The methodological utility of the natural language modality in EMO20Q can
