 descriptors, is due to the artificial nature of annotation tasks that only
 have a fixed set of options.
 By allowing an open set of natural language descriptions, the problem of
 non-prototypical emotions is traded for more complexity in analyzing natural
 language descriptions.
 We have proposed the Socratic epistemology as a way of dealing with this
 new challenge.
 
